Langata MP Nixon Korir on Saturday exchanged vows with his longtime lover Beryl Zoraima at an exclusive wedding held at the Karen Blixen Museum in Nairobi. The glamorous wedding which was well attended by close family and friends.  Kericho Senator Aaron Cheruiyot with Langata MP Nixon Korir at Karen on February 16, 2019. /COURTESY Among those in attendance at the invite-only wedding was Senate Majority leader Kipchumba Murkomen, Senators Susan Kihika (Nakuru) and Aaron Cheruiyot (Kericho).  The wedding reception venue in Karen on February 16, 2019. /COURTESY Others were MPs Charles Kanyi ‘Jaguar’ (Starehe) and John Kiarie (Dagoretti South) among others. The two lovebirds are parents to three children. The lawmaker’s wife is a lawyer working at the Kenya Pipeline company.  The groom and bridal line-up in Karen on February 16, 2019. /COURTESY The wedding took place a day after NTV anchor Dennis Okari exchanged vows with Naomi Joy in an invite-only ceremony along Kiambu Road. Okari dressed in a grey suit patterned with black was seen kissing his wife on Friday in a location that was not made public. Read: Married again: Dennis Okari kisses wife Naomi Joy in church wedding Click here for the latest political news